modules.description: This module defines configuration options for customizing the HTML output of components like tables, text blocks, rows, and columns. It allows setting CSS classes and HTML attributes for each element type, enabling precise control over styling and behavior. Use this module to configure collapsible tree structures, apply consistent class names, or add custom attributes to HTML elements in a structured way.

This module renders structured boxes as HTML, supporting raw HTML embedding, style application, and configurable output. It converts boxes into HTML strings with optional indentation and full document structure, using a flexible configuration system. The configuration submodule allows setting CSS classes and HTML attributes for elements like tables, text blocks, rows, and columns, enabling precise styling and behavior control. Use it to generate styled HTML reports or UI components, such as collapsible trees or consistently themed tables, directly from structured data.
